<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-10-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="412" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                    <head>No. 407.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Curry</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-10-22"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 22, 1886</date>.
                            (Received October 22—10 a.m.)</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Curry informs Mr. Bayard that, according to a telegram which he has
                        received on that day, he makes the renewal of the agreement depend upon the
                        inclusion therein of cargoes carried in ships of the United States from any
                        foreign country. He desires to be informed whether this condition is
                        indispensable to the conclusion of an agreement.</p>
                </div>
